341
00:29:49,504 --> 00:29:50,903
Cut a deal.

342
00:30:05,520 --> 00:30:06,509
Wait in the car.

343
00:30:07,622 --> 00:30:08,850
Don't worry.

344
00:30:09,190 --> 00:30:11,090
Everything's going to be fine.

345
00:30:11,359 --> 00:30:12,986
Please don't do anything crazy.

346
00:30:15,163 --> 00:30:17,097
Crazy's on the bus, remember?

347
00:30:20,301 --> 00:30:21,700
I love you.

348
00:30:36,150 --> 00:30:37,549
I love you too.

349
00:30:38,319 --> 00:30:39,786
Be right back.

350
00:31:15,690 --> 00:31:17,749
- Danny Roman.
- I'm going to see Niebaum.

351
00:31:17,992 --> 00:31:19,983
Could you wait a minute?
I'll buzz him.

352
00:31:22,063 --> 00:31:23,530
Wait, sir!

353
00:31:32,974 --> 00:31:33,804
Hold on.

354
00:31:34,008 --> 00:31:36,670
Roman. What can I do for you?

355
00:31:37,211 --> 00:31:39,873
Man's got a right to face his accusers,
doesn't he?

356
00:31:40,615 --> 00:31:42,810
- We need to talk.
- Go ahead, talk.

357
00:31:43,017 --> 00:31:44,279
What's going on?

358
00:31:48,656 --> 00:31:49,850
You killed your partner.

359
00:31:50,091 --> 00:31:52,616
And you're about to be
formally indicted.

360
00:31:52,860 --> 00:31:55,351
You're not answering my question.

361
00:31:55,597 --> 00:31:57,622
Nate told me you were involved. How?

362
00:32:00,802 --> 00:32:03,066
Look me in the eye and say
you weren't involved.

363
00:32:03,271 --> 00:32:05,637
- Look me in the eye!
- For what?

364
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:08,070
Why don't you just tell it to the judge?

365
00:32:08,276 --> 00:32:09,368
We're finished.

366
00:32:09,577 --> 00:32:10,703
Get him out of here.

367
00:32:10,912 --> 00:32:12,573
You're not doing this!

368
00:32:28,696 --> 00:32:30,129
Lock the door. Lock it!

369
00:32:31,099 --> 00:32:34,000
Don't make things worse than they are.
Put the gun down.

370
00:32:34,469 --> 00:32:36,300
You, sit your ass down.

371
00:32:36,504 --> 00:32:37,630
Sit!

372
00:32:40,441 --> 00:32:41,908
This is my life here, Niebaum.

373
00:32:43,678 --> 00:32:44,645
I want answers.

374
00:32:44,846 --> 00:32:45,938
I don't have answers!

375
00:32:46,147 --> 00:32:47,614
Put the gun down and leave!

376
00:32:47,815 --> 00:32:49,112
Don't feel like talking?!

377
00:32:49,350 --> 00:32:51,511
We're going to stay here until you do!

378
00:32:52,020 --> 00:32:53,612
It's your choice.

379
00:32:54,522 --> 00:32:57,491
Because I'm not going to jail today.

380
00:33:06,634 --> 00:33:07,623
Go!

381
00:33:10,938 --> 00:33:12,166
Drop your weapon.

382
00:33:12,373 --> 00:33:13,635
Drop it, Danny.

383
00:33:13,841 --> 00:33:14,773
Guns down! Down!

384
00:33:19,547 --> 00:33:23,108
That was no accident! And neither will
the next one that goes in your head!

385
00:33:23,317 --> 00:33:24,579
Get down here, now!

386
00:33:24,786 --> 00:33:25,946
Come on!

387
00:33:26,688 --> 00:33:29,748
Everybody in here, march over
to that desk over there.

388
00:33:29,991 --> 00:33:32,960
Put your guns, cuffs, keys,
everything...

389
00:33:33,161 --> 00:33:34,492
...on this desk and get out!

390
00:33:34,696 --> 00:33:36,596
Let's go! Move! Move it!

391
00:33:39,067 --> 00:33:40,295
Why are you here?

392
00:33:40,501 --> 00:33:42,196
The call is out on the city-wide.

393
00:33:42,403 --> 00:33:45,531
- See what they're making me do?!
- Danny, you just got married!

394
00:33:45,740 --> 00:33:46,729
Think about Karen!

395
00:33:48,943 --> 00:33:50,934
I am thinking about Karen.

396
00:33:52,146 --> 00:33:54,706
And now that I think of it,
I'm glad you're here.

397
00:33:54,916 --> 00:33:56,907
You just raised the ante.

398
00:33:57,819 --> 00:33:58,786
Join the party.

399
00:33:58,986 --> 00:34:00,613
God, Danny, this is crazy.

400
00:34:00,855 --> 00:34:03,983
Take your guns off.
Put them on this table now!

401
00:34:08,396 --> 00:34:10,921
I know you heard me say both of them.

402
00:34:52,573 --> 00:34:53,597
Listen to me.

403
00:34:54,041 --> 00:34:55,531
It's not too late to stop.

404
00:34:55,743 --> 00:34:57,608
Are you trying to talk me down?

405
00:34:57,812 --> 00:35:00,440
This is crazy. This isn't helping you.

406
00:35:01,449 --> 00:35:03,610
Me and him have nothing to do with this.

407
00:35:04,152 --> 00:35:06,450
I've known you 20 years.
What are you doing?

408
00:35:06,654 --> 00:35:10,454
I know I made you stay, Frost, but you
cannot monopolize the conversation.

409
00:35:10,691 --> 00:35:13,159
You're not the scene commander here.
I am.

410
00:35:15,263 --> 00:35:16,753
You're Niebaum's secretary?

411
00:35:17,465 --> 00:35:18,432
What's your name?

412
00:35:18,633 --> 00:35:20,897
My name's Maggie and I'm his assistant.

413
00:35:21,169 --> 00:35:22,830
Well, Maggie, don't be scared.

414
00:35:23,604 --> 00:35:25,970
I'm familiar with situations like this.

415
00:35:26,174 --> 00:35:29,302
I'm not scared. I've been mugged twice.
Once at gunpoint.

416
00:35:29,510 --> 00:35:31,239
Guns are not new to me.

417
00:35:31,646 --> 00:35:34,046
But I'd rather avoid them
if I get the chance.

418
00:35:34,448 --> 00:35:36,814
You won't have that chance this time.

419
00:35:37,785 --> 00:35:39,685
If you're his assistant...

420
00:35:39,887 --> 00:35:41,912
...you have everything to do with this.

421
00:35:42,523 --> 00:35:43,854
But not me, bro.

422
00:35:44,692 --> 00:35:46,660
I don't work for this pig.

423
00:35:46,861 --> 00:35:48,761
- I'm not a cop.
- You're Rudy Timmons.

424
00:35:48,963 --> 00:35:51,932
You're a rat for the rat squad.
You don't remember me?

425
00:35:52,867 --> 00:35:55,461
I arrested you in '92 for
credit card fraud.

426
00:35:58,206 --> 00:35:59,605
Yeah, I remember you.

427
00:35:59,807 --> 00:36:01,741
I remember you. Hey, man!

428
00:36:01,943 --> 00:36:04,741
Last time I saw you, you were
a clean-cut boy in blue.

429
00:36:04,946 --> 00:36:06,311
What happened to you?

430
00:36:06,514 --> 00:36:08,641
That's what we're here to find out.

431
00:36:21,729 --> 00:36:23,697
I wonder if they're out there.

432
00:36:24,532 --> 00:36:26,363
Your partners, Niebaum.

433
00:36:27,835 --> 00:36:29,496
The guilty ones.

434
00:36:30,137 --> 00:36:31,126
My guys.

435
00:36:32,740 --> 00:36:33,707
They'll come...

436
00:36:33,908 --> 00:36:36,968
...scared shitless
I'll get the truth out of you.

437
00:36:37,912 --> 00:36:39,436
And if they can't get me...

438
00:36:39,847 --> 00:36:40,836
...they'll kill you.

439
00:36:59,133 --> 00:37:01,294
Clear the perimeter and start evac.

440
00:37:05,172 --> 00:37:07,072
Nothing moves on that fucking river!

441
00:37:12,413 --> 00:37:16,144
Locate the phone panel. Lock down
the elevator. Clear the stairwell.

442
00:37:16,350 --> 00:37:19,012
Have Unit 2 hold outside
Internal Affairs.

443
00:37:21,822 --> 00:37:23,187
Christ, they're here already.

444
00:37:23,391 --> 00:37:26,952
Set up command on that barge over there
so the press can't get to us.

445
00:38:26,687 --> 00:38:27,984
What do you got?

446
00:38:28,222 --> 00:38:30,417
Elevators locked
from the 20th floor down.

447
00:38:34,829 --> 00:38:36,091
I got a real concern.

448
00:38:36,297 --> 00:38:40,666
He knows our tactics, we got a big area
to lock down. Do we have the manpower?

449
00:38:40,868 --> 00:38:43,632
We got personnel from
6 different districts.

450
00:38:43,971 --> 00:38:46,496
But he'll still try and control
the environment.

451
00:38:49,110 --> 00:38:50,668
We'll see who wins the race.

452
00:39:25,546 --> 00:39:27,878
Perpetrator is an expert marksman.

453
00:39:28,082 --> 00:39:31,017
<i>He's an expert in explosives
and tactics.</i>

454
00:39:31,285 --> 00:39:34,448
<i>Gentlemen, play this by the numbers.</i>

455
00:39:34,688 --> 00:39:36,883
<i>Maintain your fields of fire.</i>

456
00:39:45,900 --> 00:39:47,492
Elevators.

457
00:40:01,515 --> 00:40:03,676
Fucking Roman's up there, man.

458
00:40:03,884 --> 00:40:05,579
He's got Frost inside.

459
00:40:06,120 --> 00:40:08,588
We see a chance to end this,
we take him out.

460
00:40:15,396 --> 00:40:17,330
We're blind and he's seeing 20/20.

461
00:40:18,732 --> 00:40:22,361
I want visuals and audio
set up from 19 and 21.

462
00:40:22,570 --> 00:40:23,696
Farley, you're negotiating.

463
00:40:23,904 --> 00:40:24,871
He'll eat Farley up.

464
00:40:25,072 --> 00:40:25,936
Commander...

465
00:40:27,141 --> 00:40:29,575
...if you want to talk to him...

466
00:40:29,910 --> 00:40:31,104
I may not have a choice.

467
00:40:31,312 --> 00:40:35,476
Get him locked down first! In the
meantime get on the fucking phone.

468
00:40:37,885 --> 00:40:39,614
Someone locate the building engineer.

469
00:40:39,820 --> 00:40:41,014
Right away.

470
00:40:59,306 --> 00:41:00,967
Chief Travis.

471
00:41:03,777 --> 00:41:05,574
Special Agent Grey.

472
00:41:05,779 --> 00:41:06,746
This is Moran.

473
00:41:07,047 --> 00:41:09,208
We're the FBI negotiators.

474
00:41:10,184 --> 00:41:13,176
It's a federal building.
It's our jurisdiction.

475
00:41:13,387 --> 00:41:15,412
He's one of ours. We got this.

476
00:41:15,656 --> 00:41:17,556
Fine with us. For now.

477
00:41:25,332 --> 00:41:26,196
We got eyes.

478
00:41:42,216 --> 00:41:43,945
Son of a bitch! Go to camera 2.

479
00:42:05,039 --> 00:42:06,506
He got all 6. We got nothing.

480
00:42:08,275 --> 00:42:10,368
We got to see in that room.

481
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:14,838
No eyes, no ears.

482
00:42:15,449 --> 00:42:16,916
We're running out of options.

483
00:42:17,117 --> 00:42:20,109
- I want status reports now.
- Give me an update.

484
00:42:22,623 --> 00:42:25,854
<i>Give me status. Somebody give
me status. Tell me what you see.</i>

485
00:42:26,260 --> 00:42:28,228
