00:42:33,300 --> 00:42:34,198
We contained him.

489
00:42:34,401 --> 00:42:38,633
We have not contained him.
He's contained himself and cut us off.

490
00:42:38,839 --> 00:42:41,273
Try the phone again.
Let's see what he wants.

491
00:42:47,848 --> 00:42:48,906
Talk.

492
00:42:56,523 --> 00:43:00,015
I'm Rudy, so don't shoot me
thinking I'm him. Please.

493
00:43:02,296 --> 00:43:04,059
Rudy, my name is Farley.

494
00:43:05,266 --> 00:43:06,699
Please get Danny on the line.

495
00:43:07,434 --> 00:43:09,334
Farley would like to talk to you.

496
00:43:09,703 --> 00:43:11,694
I only want to talk to Chris Sabian.

497
00:43:14,341 --> 00:43:16,468
He'll only talk to Chris Sabian.

498
00:43:17,111 --> 00:43:18,635
<i>If Sabian's not here in 20 minutes...</i>

499
00:43:19,513 --> 00:43:20,343
...you die.

500
00:43:21,849 --> 00:43:25,546
I don't want to talk to anyone else
but Chris Sabian.

501
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:28,283
Okay, we heard you.

502
00:43:30,591 --> 00:43:32,115
He said they heard you.

503
00:43:42,670 --> 00:43:43,898
Who is Chris Sabian?

504
00:43:44,772 --> 00:43:46,933
- I heard of him.
- He's from the Westside.

505
00:43:47,141 --> 00:43:50,736
Once he talked 55 hours.
Never forces tactical action.

506
00:43:51,612 --> 00:43:53,409
I don't know how Danny knows him.

507
00:43:56,950 --> 00:43:57,746
So find Sabian.

508
00:43:57,951 --> 00:43:59,782
911 Chris Sabian.

509
00:44:05,426 --> 00:44:06,620
Come on...

510
00:44:07,261 --> 00:44:08,523
...talk to me.

511
00:44:10,097 --> 00:44:11,291
I'm right here.

512
00:44:11,498 --> 00:44:15,491
I'm not going anywhere,
so please come out.

513
00:44:16,337 --> 00:44:18,737
You don't want me to.
I want to kill her.

514
00:44:18,939 --> 00:44:22,102
I do want you to come out,
so we can discuss this.

515
00:44:23,310 --> 00:44:25,039
You're not even listening to me.

516
00:44:25,746 --> 00:44:27,577
Yes, I am listening to you.

517
00:44:28,015 --> 00:44:30,381
You promised that you'd come out.

518
00:44:30,784 --> 00:44:32,445
So come on out, all right?

519
00:44:32,653 --> 00:44:34,985
I don't want to do this
through the door.

520
00:44:38,792 --> 00:44:42,956
Look, I want to do something
without arguing. Let's get on the road.

521
00:44:43,163 --> 00:44:45,427
Your clothes look fine.

522
00:44:45,866 --> 00:44:47,197
They do.

523
00:44:47,568 --> 00:44:51,231
According to some people
I look fat in ski clothes.

524
00:44:51,438 --> 00:44:53,599
That's not the word she used.
She used...

525
00:44:56,543 --> 00:44:57,976
...a much worse word.

526
00:45:00,581 --> 00:45:02,572
Honey, get off the phone!

527
00:45:03,217 --> 00:45:04,445
Get off the phone.

528
00:45:05,386 --> 00:45:06,614
Get off the phone.

529
00:45:06,954 --> 00:45:09,616
I'm your father and I'm very
upset with you right now!

530
00:45:10,924 --> 00:45:12,255
Try your sweater.

531
00:45:13,026 --> 00:45:14,459
Honey, get off the phone.

532
00:45:14,728 --> 00:45:17,196
And I want you to apologize to your
mother for saying she looks...

533
00:45:19,066 --> 00:45:20,192
..."wide."

534
00:45:22,403 --> 00:45:26,100
That is not a good word to use. "Wide."
How'd you like to be called wide?

535
00:45:26,306 --> 00:45:30,037
Do you hear me?! I am very serious!
I'm very angry with you!

536
00:45:30,244 --> 00:45:32,508
Get off the phone! Get off the phone.

537
00:45:33,714 --> 00:45:35,011
Don't you make me...

538
00:45:36,717 --> 00:45:38,981
I talked a man out of
blowing up the Sears Tower...

539
00:45:39,186 --> 00:45:42,246
...but I can't talk my wife out
of a bedroom or my kid off a phone.

540
00:45:42,489 --> 00:45:46,050
That's because no one's standing
behind you with a big gun.

541
00:45:47,361 --> 00:45:49,295
Yeah, well, that's debatable.

542
00:45:49,530 --> 00:45:51,020
Hold on.

543
00:45:54,268 --> 00:45:55,496
Yeah, he's right here.

544
00:45:56,203 --> 00:45:57,329
It's for you.

545
00:46:05,012 --> 00:46:06,604
Sabian's 20 minutes out.

546
00:46:07,614 --> 00:46:09,081
And we only got 15.

547
00:46:09,283 --> 00:46:11,547
Call Danny again.
Get him to change that deadline.

548
00:46:12,686 --> 00:46:14,278
Tell him Sabian's on his way.

549
00:46:23,664 --> 00:46:24,460
Sabian?

550
00:46:27,167 --> 00:46:28,259
It's Farley.

551
00:46:28,535 --> 00:46:31,834
I told you I don't want to talk
to anyone but Chris Sabian.

552
00:46:32,072 --> 00:46:36,304
He's on his way. He's going to be here
real soon. We just need more time.

553
00:46:37,077 --> 00:46:39,477
But you don't have more time, Farley.

554
00:46:40,914 --> 00:46:43,314
What are you doing here?
This is pretty serious.

555
00:46:43,584 --> 00:46:46,280
It is serious!
So why don't you take me seriously?

556
00:46:46,487 --> 00:46:48,921
Well, we are. We are. We just...

557
00:46:50,958 --> 00:46:52,755
I just want to talk to you, okay?

558
00:46:53,026 --> 00:46:53,958
Wait, wait.

559
00:46:54,294 --> 00:46:55,955
You think you can talk me down?

560
00:46:58,398 --> 00:46:59,660
I need to...

561
00:47:00,567 --> 00:47:01,761
Tell me what you want.

562
00:47:04,972 --> 00:47:06,200
You want a shot?

563
00:47:06,507 --> 00:47:08,134
I'll give you a shot.

564
00:47:08,342 --> 00:47:11,334
We got some time before Sabian gets
here.

565
00:47:12,012 --> 00:47:13,980
What do I want? Let's see.

566
00:47:14,281 --> 00:47:15,942
How about, can I see a priest?

567
00:47:17,317 --> 00:47:18,750
No, you can't see a priest.

568
00:47:18,952 --> 00:47:21,944
<i>That's good, Farley.
You shouldn't let me see a priest.</i>

569
00:47:22,256 --> 00:47:26,192
A priest is associated with death and
you don't want me thinking about death.

570
00:47:28,729 --> 00:47:31,129
But you told me "no," Farley.
You can't say "no."

571
00:47:31,365 --> 00:47:33,799
Never use "no" in a hostage situation.

572
00:47:34,201 --> 00:47:36,965
<i>- Danny, would you relax a little bit?
- I'm relaxed!</i>

573
00:47:37,170 --> 00:47:38,501
<i>But here's some advice.</i>

574
00:47:38,705 --> 00:47:42,106
Never say "no" to a hostage-taker.
It's in the manual.

575
00:47:42,376 --> 00:47:43,968
Will you to tell me "no" again?

576
00:47:44,244 --> 00:47:45,233
No.

577
00:47:45,579 --> 00:47:46,978
<i>Wrong answer!</i>

578
00:47:47,814 --> 00:47:48,712
Shut up!

579
00:47:48,982 --> 00:47:52,782
<i>Never use "no," "don't," "won't"
or "can't." All right?</i>

580
00:47:53,053 --> 00:47:57,547
It eliminates options. The option that
leaves is to shoot someone. Understand?

581
00:47:57,824 --> 00:47:58,688
Yes.

582
00:47:58,892 --> 00:48:01,360
<i>Yes! Good! See, "yes" is good.</i>

583
00:48:01,628 --> 00:48:06,327
You say "no" again, I'll kill somebody.
Let's practice. Can I see a priest?

584
00:48:07,000 --> 00:48:09,969
You know what? Can we just
talk about this right now?

585
00:48:10,203 --> 00:48:13,639
You wanted to talk! We are talking!
Now, can I see a priest?

586
00:48:14,474 --> 00:48:15,998
I'll see what I can do?

587
00:48:16,743 --> 00:48:19,211
<i>That's good, Farley.
Now you're learning.</i>

588
00:48:19,947 --> 00:48:22,211
I'd like a submachine gun
to blow everyone away.

589
00:48:23,350 --> 00:48:24,681
I'll look into that.

590
00:48:24,885 --> 00:48:26,216
<i>You're doing good.</i>

591
00:48:26,987 --> 00:48:28,249
You ever cheat on your wife?

592
00:48:29,456 --> 00:48:30,445
<i>- No.
- Watch yourself.</i>

593
00:48:30,791 --> 00:48:32,224
I'll kill someone.

594
00:48:33,393 --> 00:48:35,486
<i>You ever cheat on your wife? Answer!</i>

595
00:48:36,063 --> 00:48:37,394
I'll see what I can do.

596
00:48:38,632 --> 00:48:41,624
<i>I'll have to think about that.
I'll look into that.</i>

597
00:48:41,969 --> 00:48:43,630
You ever...

598
00:48:43,837 --> 00:48:46,601
...dress up like a schoolgirl and
get your ass spanked?

599
00:48:47,407 --> 00:48:50,467
Look, all I want to do is talk to you.

600
00:48:50,777 --> 00:48:51,641
I am talking!

601
00:48:51,845 --> 00:48:56,111
Did you or did you not dress up like a
schoolgirl and get your ass spanked?

602
00:48:57,451 --> 00:48:59,442
Have to look into that, Danny.

603
00:48:59,720 --> 00:49:02,314
Nothing against you dressing up
like a girl...

604
00:49:02,689 --> 00:49:04,919
<i>... but I didn't know that
about you, Farley.</i>

605
00:49:05,759 --> 00:49:07,727
This is really, really unproductive.

606
00:49:08,061 --> 00:49:09,050
Unproductive?!

607
00:49:09,730 --> 00:49:10,924
<i>You're right. It is.</i>

608
00:49:11,264 --> 00:49:14,256
<i>So tell me a joke, Farley.
You know any jokes?</i>

609
00:49:15,702 --> 00:49:19,468
No?! You just cost someone
their life, Farley! Game over!!

610
00:49:20,674 --> 00:49:21,834
Shot fired!

611
00:49:24,511 --> 00:49:25,603
Shot fired!

612
00:49:25,879 --> 00:49:26,868
<i>Can anyone see?</i>

613
00:49:32,886 --> 00:49:34,114
Don't let him go.

614
00:49:36,556 --> 00:49:38,080
You can't talk me down!

615
00:49:38,325 --> 00:49:40,657
<i>You can't make me change the deadline!</i>

616
00:49:40,927 --> 00:49:42,895
Now get me Sabian!

617
00:49:43,130 --> 00:49:46,964
You got 6 minutes, 42, 41...

618
00:49:47,267 --> 00:49:49,735
<i>Listen, Danny, is anybody hurt?!</i>

619
00:49:50,037 --> 00:49:50,969
Is anybody hurt?

620
00:49:51,304 --> 00:49:54,432
We're okay, just don't be saying "no"
no more, motherfucker!

621
00:49:57,044 --> 00:49:59,945
- Everybody calm down.
- I'm so sorry.

622
00:50:00,247 --> 00:50:01,839
I'm so fucking sorry.

623
00:50:02,449 --> 00:50:04,679
<i>Give me status. Someone give me status.</i>

624
00:50:04,885 --> 00:50:06,147
<i>Tell me what you see.</i>

625
00:50:06,920 --> 00:50:08,478
Visibility zero, sir.

626
00:50:12,626 --> 00:50:13,854
<i>Just a few moments ago...</i>

627
00:50:14,094 --> 00:50:17,996
<i>... a single shot was fired inside
the city administration building.</i>

628
00:50:20,300 --> 00:50:23,463
We got the whole city of Chicago
watching this.

629
00:50:24,304 --> 00:50:27,068
This could turn into a press nightmare.

630
00:50:29,609 --> 00:50:32,305
What do we do if Sabian can't make it?

631
00:50:33,780 --> 00:50:36,271
We got to remember that's
Danny Roman upstairs.

632
00:50:36,483 --> 00:50:39,418
We work with him and we don't
really know what he's done.

633
00:50:39,619 --> 00:50:41,348
We know what he's doing now.

634
00:50:44,991 --> 00:50:47,960
I don't want this to get personal
for us either.

635
00:50:48,962 --> 00:50:51,226
He's obviously over...
Do you mind?!

636
00:50:59,106 --> 00:51:01,131
He's obviously gone over the edge.

637
00:51:01,341 --> 00:51:02,638
This is not personal.

638
00:51:03,510 --> 00:51:07,970
If I thought sending my team in there
would put more people in jeopardy...

639
00:51:08,181 --> 00:51:09,648
...I wouldn't consider it.

640
00:51:12,519 --> 00:51:13,816
I don't want to go in there.

641
00:51:14,254 --> 00:51:15,778
But it's our best option.

642
00:51:16,022 --> 00:51:17,489
He can't be talked down.

643
00:51:18,425 --> 00:51:19,892
They'll get us out.

644
00:51:20,360 --> 00:51:22,692
Don't worry about Danny.
He won't hurt anybody.

645
00:51:22,896 --> 00:51:26,423
Bullshit. No one knows what this
crazy fucker is going to do.

646
00:51:26,800 --> 00:51:31,635
This has nothing to do with me
and Maggie. You get him to let us go.

647
00:51:32,038 --> 00:51:35,166
"Because once you familiarize yourself
with the chains of bondage...

648
00:51:35,575 --> 00:51:38,203
...you prepare your own
limbs to wear them."

649
00:51:38,411 --> 00:51:40,675
Abraham Lincoln said that
and I believe it.

650
00:51:40,881 --> 00:51:44,214
So you have got to get me
the fuck out! Now!

651
00:51:46,086 --> 00:51:48,816
Do yourself a favor and keep quiet.
We'll handle this.

652
00:51:49,055 --> 00:51:50,818
Don't tell me to be quiet.

653
00:51:51,057 --> 00:51:55,858
Don't say you'll handle it. None of you
been in a situation like this before.

654
00:51:56,062 --> 00:51:57,222
Just shut the fuck up.

655
00:51:57,430 --> 00:51:59,193
Fuck you!

656
00:51:59,432 --> 00:52:01,423
- Prick.
- That's enough!

657
00:52:01,668 --> 00:52:04,967
He's going to hear you.
He's got the gun, so he's in charge.

658
00:52:06,039 --> 00:52:07,506
Both of you pipe down now.

659
00:52:13,246 --> 00:52:16,647
Let Maggie go. She's not involved.
And she's a woman...

660
00:52:17,050 --> 00:52:21,009
I didn't ask to be let go because
I'm a woman. I hate that crap.

661
00:52:22,489 --> 00:52:24,889
Me and him should be let go because
we had nothing to do with this.

662
00:52:25,492 --> 00:52:26,652
It's between you cops.

663
00:52:26,893 --> 00:52:28,918
We have nothing to do with this.

664
00:52:30,831 --> 00:52:34,267
Look, I'm not just some dirt merchant
loose in the street anymore.

665
00:52:34,467 --> 00:52:37,903
I'm not. I got a nice new lady friend
that I'd like to get back to.

666
00:52:38,104 --> 00:52:40,868
And she has got this kid, Albert.

667
00:52:41,074 --> 00:52:42,098
Super kid, Dan.

668
00:52:42,475 --> 00:52:43,442
Great kid.

669
00:52:43,643 --> 00:52:45,406
What do you think you can do?

670
00:52:45,812 --> 00:52:47,473
Take a look at that screen.

671
00:52:48,081 --> 00:52:49,878
They think you're a killer.

672
00:52:50,550 --> 00:52:52,484
They're going to try to take you out.

673
00:52:52,686 --> 00:52:55,917
What do you think Sabian can do?
He can't stop this.

674
00:52:56,156 --> 00:52:57,714
What about you, Frosty?

675
00:52:58,158 --> 00:52:59,989
You think I'm a killer too?

676
00:53:00,794 --> 00:53:01,761
Come on!

677
00:53:01,995 --> 00:53:04,828
You've known me for 20 years.

678
00:53:06,666 --> 00:53:07,894
You think I killed Nate?

679
00:53:13,506 --> 00:53:15,497
I don't know what to think.

680
00:53:16,910 --> 00:53:18,309
I'll tell you this:

681
00:53:19,512 --> 00:53:21,343
What you're doing is not helping.

682
00:53:39,599 --> 00:53:41,191
<i>Hey, schoolgirl.</i>

683
00:53:43,003 --> 00:53:46,530
<i>You still sweating that ugly display
you gave us all a few minutes ago?</i>

684
00:53:47,340 --> 00:53:50,867
Stop kicking yourself in the ass.
We all have our bad days.

685
00:53:51,878 --> 00:53:54,813
<i>Stop trying to get in here.
I'm pretty well bunkered.</i>

686
00:53:55,015 --> 00:53:55,947
<i>Palermo...</i>

687
00:53:56,483 --> 00:53:58,075
...take that toothpick out.

688
00:53:58,551 --> 00:54:01,349
<i>I don't want you to swallow it
if something goes down.</i>

689
00:54:01,588 --> 00:54:03,749
That's right, sports fans...

690
00:54:03,990 --> 00:54:05,855
...it's me, Danny Roman.

691
00:54:06,059 --> 00:54:07,924
The man upstairs.

692
00:54:08,395 --> 00:54:11,990
Just wanted to say hello before the
curtain goes up on this little drama.

693
00:54:14,100 --> 00:54:16,330
<i>I guess you're all wondering
why we're here.</i>

694
00:54:16,803 --> 00:54:18,327
Well, it's simple.

695
00:54:19,239 --> 00:54:21,366
<i>We're here to find out
who took our money...</i>

696
00:54:22,008 --> 00:54:23,441
...and who killed Nate...

697
00:54:23,643 --> 00:54:25,042
...because it wasn't me.

698
00:54:25,979 --> 00:54:28,209
There's some bad cops among us...

699
00:54:28,415 --> 00:54:31,976
<i>... and today we're going to
find out who they are.</i>

700
00:54:33,186 --> 00:54:34,653
<i>I know how that sounds.</i>

701
00:54:35,221 --> 00:54:36,711
<i>I know what you're thinking:</i>

702
00:54:36,957 --> 00:54:39,585
"He's gone. He's a murderer."

703
00:54:40,860 --> 00:54:43,988
But I'm that same son of a bitch
you trusted your lives with...

704
00:54:44,197 --> 00:54:46,757
...played softball with,
went drinking with.

705
00:54:47,033 --> 00:54:49,934
The same guy you invited to your house
to celebrate...

706
00:54:50,203 --> 00:54:51,761
<i>... your kid's baptism, Tonray.</i>

707
00:54:52,005 --> 00:54:53,870
<i>The same guy who saved Palermo's ass...</i>

708
00:54:54,074 --> 00:54:57,066
<i>... when that sniper had a bead
on him at the stadium gig.</i>

709
00:54:57,610 --> 00:54:58,599
This is good.

710
00:54:59,846 --> 00:55:03,282
Danny's trying to get us to Stockholm
so we think twice about taking him out.

711
00:55:04,684 --> 00:55:06,015
Now, I want...

712
00:55:06,753 --> 00:55:08,846
No, I need you guys...

713
00:55:09,089 --> 00:55:11,751
<i>... to understand that I had
no choice here.</i>

714
00:55:12,826 --> 00:55:15,294
My life was being stripped away from me.

715
00:55:16,596 --> 00:55:18,223
First, they kill Nate.

716
00:55:22,435 --> 00:55:24,232
Then they took my badge.

717
00:55:25,105 --> 00:55:26,265
Then you guys.

718
00:55:27,440 --> 00:55:28,270
<i>Next...</i>

719
00:55:29,175 --> 00:55:33,976
...they were going to take away my wife
by sending me to prison. And that...

720
00:55:35,081 --> 00:55:36,571
...I cannot take.

721
00:55:38,051 --> 00:55:39,882
I can't live without...

722
00:55:46,760 --> 00:55:48,694
<i>Put yourself in my position.</i>

723
00:55:50,296 --> 00:55:51,627
<i>What else could I do?</i>

724
00:55:52,265 --> 00:55:56,463
Gaines, get word out to our team. We're
switching to frequency 3 now.

725
00:55:57,604 --> 00:56:01,472
I tried to tell everyone I was being
set up, but no one wanted to listen.

726
00:56:02,142 --> 00:56:04,110
<i>Well, now you have no choice.</i>

727
00:56:04,310 --> 00:56:06,870
You got to listen,
because we're not leaving here...

728
00:56:07,080 --> 00:56:09,605
...until I find out who set me up.

729
00:56:11,518 --> 00:56:12,849
Let me warn you:

730
00:56:13,319 --> 00:56:17,050
Whoever killed Nate is frightened that
Niebaum might know something.

731
00:56:17,724 --> 00:56:20,124
They're going to try and
end this quickly.

732
00:56:20,727 --> 00:56:22,194
Another warning:

733
00:56:23,329 --> 00:56:25,263
I know the rules of engagement...

734
00:56:25,498 --> 00:56:27,329
<i>... so don't test me.</i>

735
00:56:29,769 --> 00:56:32,169
You got 4 minutes to get Sabian here...

736
00:56:32,505 --> 00:56:35,702
...or you'll find out just how serious
I really am.

737
00:56:52,158 --> 00:56:53,557
Look me in the eye.

738
00:56:55,161 --> 00:56:56,526
Right here.

739
00:56:57,931 --> 00:56:58,955
Now, tell me...

740
00:57:00,366 --> 00:57:03,995
...when did you find out Nate
was investigating the fund?

741
00:57:13,546 --> 00:57:16,709
I first found that Nathan was
conducting the investigation...

742
00:57:16,916 --> 00:57:19,146
...after I spoke with you
after he was killed.

743
00:57:20,353 --> 00:57:23,220
You're lying. And I know you're lying.

744
00:57:23,456 --> 00:57:24,388
You know it, huh?

745
00:57:24,591 --> 00:57:26,422
You can read my mind, Roman?

746
00:57:26,626 --> 00:57:29,390
No, I'm not. I'm reading your eyes.

747
00:57:29,729 --> 00:57:31,162
The eyes can't lie.

748
00:57:32,432 --> 00:57:34,127
Didn't you know?!

749
00:57:35,235 --> 00:57:39,171
A quick lesson in lying. See, this is
what us real cops do.

750
00:57:39,372 --> 00:57:40,930
We study liars.

751
00:57:41,141 --> 00:57:42,199
Example:

752
00:57:42,408 --> 00:57:45,969
If I ask you a question about something
visual, like your favorite color...

753
00:57:46,246 --> 00:57:48,908
...your eyes go up and to the left.

754
00:57:49,115 --> 00:57:52,050
Neurophysiology tells us your eyes
go in that direction...

755
00:57:52,252 --> 00:57:54,652
...because you're accessing
the visual cortex.

756
00:57:54,854 --> 00:57:56,378
So you're telling the truth.

757
00:57:57,223 --> 00:57:59,748
If your eyes go up and right...

758
00:57:59,993 --> 00:58:03,360
...you're accessing the brain's creative
centers and we know you're full of shit.

759
00:58:04,430 --> 00:58:06,557
Now, let's try this again.

760
00:58:06,933 --> 00:58:08,400
Your favorite television show?

761
00:58:09,435 --> 00:58:12,268
I'm not going to play your stupid
fucking game, okay?

762
00:58:12,472 --> 00:58:15,270
Why, Niebaum? You afraid we'll
catch you in a lie?

763
00:58:18,811 --> 00:58:21,279
When did you find out
Nate was investigating the fund?

764
00:58:22,615 --> 00:58:23,775
After I spoke with you.

765
00:58:23,983 --> 00:58:26,076
That's a lie if I've ever seen one!

766
00:58:26,286 --> 00:58:30,279
- Fuck you! I never blinked my eyes!
- You didn't have to blink.

767
00:58:30,523 --> 00:58:32,457
Your body language says you're lying.

768
00:58:32,659 --> 00:58:34,889
He's nervous.
What do you expect from him?

769
00:58:35,094 --> 00:58:36,857
Shut up! You know how this works!

770
00:58:37,597 --> 00:58:40,065
It's not just your eyes.
It's everything.

771
00:58:40,300 --> 00:58:43,633
If you cough, sneeze, cross your legs,
scratch your ass...

772
00:58:43,836 --> 00:58:46,031
...they're all tell-tale signs.

773
00:58:46,239 --> 00:58:49,436
You can stare at me with those
dead-ass eyes all you want.

774
00:58:49,642 --> 00:58:51,234
You can't beat the system.

775
00:58:51,844 --> 00:58:52,902
One last question:

776
00:58:56,916 --> 00:58:58,611
Do you know who killed Nate?

777
00:59:06,693 --> 00:59:07,682
You.

778
00:59:10,663 --> 00:59:12,460
I don't know. I couldn't tell.

779
00:59:12,665 --> 00:59:13,529
Up, down, right, left...

780
00:59:15,335 --> 00:59:16,666
So what now? Card tricks?

781
00:59:17,337 --> 00:59:18,531
Shut the fuck up!

782
00:59:18,738 --> 00:59:22,196
You knew Nate was investigating
the fund and you killed him.

783
00:59:23,343 --> 00:59:24,674
You could've ended this.

784
00:59:24,877 --> 00:59:26,811
I guess you don't want to.

785
00:59:27,146 --> 00:59:28,477
That's too bad.

786
00:59:29,482 --> 00:59:31,347
That's really too bad.

787
00:59:33,820 --> 00:59:36,482
Because Danny Roman was just
starting to like you.

788
00:59:37,390 --> 00:59:39,551
Tell Danny Roman to hold the fuck on.

789
00:59:42,562 --> 00:59:43,893
You don't want to do this.

790
00:59:44,063 --> 00:59:44,961
How do you know?

791
00:59:46,065 --> 00:59:49,694
If you think I could kill Nate, how do
you know I don't want to do this?

792
01:00:01,447 --> 01:00:02,914
Danny Roman?

793
01:00:03,316 --> 01:00:04,783
This is Chris Sabian here.

794
01:00:04,984 --> 01:00:07,544
Good timing, Chris.
You made it just in time.

795
01:00:08,755 --> 01:00:11,246
I got lucky. Traffic was light.

796
01:00:11,491 --> 01:00:13,186
<i>Glad you accepted my invitation.</i>

797
01:00:13,426 --> 01:00:16,884
I wouldn't have missed it for the world.
What's it been? 2 years?

798
01:00:17,096 --> 01:00:18,154
<i>Not since we both...</i>

799
01:00:18,364 --> 01:00:20,332
...showed for that North Side gig.

800
01:00:20,566 --> 01:00:22,727
You pulled rank and ran my boys out.

801
01:00:23,002 --> 01:00:24,936
Two negotiators on the same site...

802
01:00:25,338 --> 01:00:26,532
<i>... never work.</i>

803
01:00:26,873 --> 01:00:30,274
So what's this, then? The exception
that disproves the rule?

804
01:00:31,344 --> 01:00:36,304
You do your job, I do mine, maybe we
both walk out of here in one piece.

805
01:00:40,386 --> 01:00:42,479
Here's the million-dollar question.

806
01:00:43,056 --> 01:00:43,988
Why you?

807
01:00:44,624 --> 01:00:45,989
Exactly.

808
01:00:46,459 --> 01:00:50,293
I don't want to go into that now.
We'll talk about that later.

809
01:00:50,763 --> 01:00:53,755
This is our first date.
The courting period.

810
01:00:57,003 --> 01:01:00,734
<i>So what do guys like you do when
they're not talking guys like me down?</i>

811
01:01:02,442 --> 01:01:06,902
I'm pretty much of a homebody.
I spend a lot of time with my family.

812
01:01:08,448 --> 01:01:09,346
My kid.

813
01:01:09,982 --> 01:01:12,212
I read a lot of books.

814
01:01:12,418 --> 01:01:15,387
<i>I watch a lot of old movies. AMC.</i>

815
01:01:15,621 --> 01:01:18,351
You got a satellite?
They show all those old westerns.

816
01:01:18,791 --> 01:01:20,053
Westerns?

817
01:01:20,793 --> 01:01:22,090
I like comedies, myself.

818
01:01:22,662 --> 01:01:24,391
<i>I did like Shane though.</i>

819
01:01:25,732 --> 01:01:27,222
<i>Shane, now that's a good one.</i>

820
01:01:27,633 --> 01:01:31,330
I would have picked one where
the hero lives at the end.

821
01:01:31,537 --> 01:01:33,596
<i>Like a Rio Bravo...</i>

822
01:01:33,806 --> 01:01:35,330
<i>...or a Red River.</i>

823
01:01:35,808 --> 01:01:37,799
<i>I think that's the wrong movie.</i>

824
01:01:38,010 --> 01:01:41,343
Shane lives. At the end of it,
he's riding off and that kid...

825
01:01:41,614 --> 01:01:43,275
<i>- Brandon...
- De Wilde.</i>

826
01:01:43,483 --> 01:01:46,941
Brandon de Wilde's calling his name:
"Shane, come back! Shane!"

827
01:01:47,954 --> 01:01:50,980
I'm sorry to be the one to
tell you this but Shane died.

828
01:01:51,224 --> 01:01:53,055
That's an assumption.

829
01:01:53,659 --> 01:01:55,627
It's a common mistake.

830
01:01:56,396 --> 01:01:58,796
In the final shot,
he slumps over his horse.

831
01:01:58,998 --> 01:02:01,626
He doesn't look back because he can't.
Shane's dead.

832
01:02:02,101 --> 01:02:04,626
<i>He slumps because he's shot.
Don't mean he's dead.</i>

833
01:02:04,837 --> 01:02:07,067
You think Butch and Sundance live too?

834
01:02:07,273 --> 01:02:10,367
You never see them dead either,
but they're surrounded.

835
01:02:10,576 --> 01:02:12,305
Now you're a history buff?

836
01:02:12,612 --> 01:02:14,876
I generally read
histories and biographies.

837
01:02:15,081 --> 01:02:16,981
Don't believe everything you read.

838
01:02:17,450 --> 01:02:19,441
I didn't say I read just one book.

839
01:02:19,652 --> 01:02:23,281
I try to read all books on a subject.
You know, try to get all the facts...

840
01:02:23,656 --> 01:02:26,181
...and then decide for myself
what really happened.

841
01:02:27,427 --> 01:02:29,918
Get all the facts, huh? That's smart.

842
01:02:30,163 --> 01:02:32,290
You're much better at this than Farley.

843
01:02:32,665 --> 01:02:35,600
<i>All right, before we start to bore
everyone, let's get back to business.</i>

844
01:02:35,868 --> 01:02:37,859
<i>First, my list of demands.</i>

845
01:02:40,706 --> 01:02:43,072
One: I want my badge brought down here.

846
01:02:43,743 --> 01:02:46,143
Two: If I die, I want a
departmental funeral.

847
01:02:46,345 --> 01:02:47,642
No one's dying here.

848
01:02:47,847 --> 01:02:49,747
<i>Three: I want the informant found.</i>

849
01:02:49,949 --> 01:02:52,281
He's the only one who
can clear my name...

850
01:02:52,485 --> 01:02:54,510
...and knows who's running
this conspiracy.

851
01:02:54,754 --> 01:02:57,484
Four: I want to know
who killed my partner.

852
01:02:57,723 --> 01:03:01,284
If neither the informant or killer
is found in 8 hours...

853
01:03:01,527 --> 01:03:04,462
...I will kill one hostage an hour
until they're all dead.

854
01:03:04,697 --> 01:03:05,823
Five:

855
01:03:06,032 --> 01:03:08,330
I want to talk to you face to face now.

856
01:03:13,039 --> 01:03:15,667
- Scene commander's upstairs?
- You can talk to me.

857
01:03:15,875 --> 01:03:17,035
You're the chief?

858
01:03:17,777 --> 01:03:19,642
Pleased to meet you.
You're Beck?

859
01:03:21,113 --> 01:03:22,102
You're...?

860
01:03:25,051 --> 01:03:26,780
All right. Vest.

861
01:03:27,720 --> 01:03:28,744
You're going up?

862
01:03:28,988 --> 01:03:29,977
Yes.

863
01:03:30,323 --> 01:03:34,225
- Why didn't you try and talk him down?
- He would've expected it. His sheet.

864
01:03:36,562 --> 01:03:37,927
Why'd he ask for me?

865
01:03:38,130 --> 01:03:40,098
We were hoping you could answer that.

866
01:03:40,366 --> 01:03:41,890
Psych evaluation, who's on it?

867
01:03:43,336 --> 01:03:44,530
He thinks he's innocent.

868
01:03:44,737 --> 01:03:48,002
We'll probably have to go tactical.
We've put a plan together.

869
01:03:48,207 --> 01:03:51,904
If we can distract him long enough,
we can send in an infiltration team.

870
01:03:52,144 --> 01:03:54,374
- Let's wait on that.
- Wife's here!

871
01:03:56,549 --> 01:03:59,712
God! How is he? Has he hurt anyone?
Who's talking to him?

872
01:03:59,919 --> 01:04:01,477
Karen, he's okay.

873
01:04:01,721 --> 01:04:03,211
He asked for Chris Sabian.

874
01:04:03,589 --> 01:04:04,556
I'm Chris Sabian.

875
01:04:05,424 --> 01:04:06,550
Do you know Danny?

876
01:04:08,127 --> 01:04:11,528
He didn't do those things they say.
You have to help him.

877
01:04:11,797 --> 01:04:14,391
I have no idea about Danny's
guilt or innocence.

878
01:04:14,934 --> 01:04:17,494
I'm here to get him out safely.
If you want to help...

879
01:04:17,703 --> 01:04:20,228
...answer Tonray's questions
and then go home.

880
01:04:20,573 --> 01:04:22,700
No! No! I'm not going home.

881
01:04:25,244 --> 01:04:28,736
You bring tension and emotion to a scene
that already has too much of both.

882
01:04:29,415 --> 01:04:30,507
I am not...

883
01:04:30,716 --> 01:04:32,183
...leaving my husband.

884
01:04:35,755 --> 01:04:38,588
All right, fine. But if you want
to help him, help me.

885
01:04:38,824 --> 01:04:40,917
I have to get up there now.

886
01:04:41,160 --> 01:04:45,756
Go with Tonray, answer his questions
and then stay in case we need you.

887
01:04:45,965 --> 01:04:49,423
Just come with me and talk, okay?
It's going to be all right.

888
01:04:56,042 --> 01:04:57,202
How do I get up?

889
01:04:57,410 --> 01:05:00,402
Freight elevator to 18,
and walk the rest of the way.

890
01:05:00,613 --> 01:05:04,606
All right. What is this? This is a
shaft off Internal Affairs?

891
01:05:04,817 --> 01:05:07,411
That's access to the steam pipes.
It's unusable.

892
01:05:07,887 --> 01:05:10,378
First, get his badge.
Second, shut off the heat.

893
01:05:10,856 --> 01:05:13,950
He might deal a hostage to get it back.
What channel?

894
01:05:14,193 --> 01:05:15,160
Three.

895
01:05:16,329 --> 01:05:17,694
I want to show you something.

896
01:05:19,599 --> 01:05:21,191
Danny, take me.

897
01:05:22,635 --> 01:05:24,398
Take him. Come on.

898
01:05:24,704 --> 01:05:26,399
I got the asthma.

899
01:05:26,606 --> 01:05:27,630
You know?

900
01:05:29,375 --> 01:05:32,310
You can't put me in bad situations, man.

901
01:05:33,012 --> 01:05:36,709
For chrissakes.
Why you always pick on me?

902
01:05:37,016 --> 01:05:39,576
I mean, who am I?
Charlie Brown?

903
01:05:40,019 --> 01:05:41,850
You know what Nietzsche says:

904
01:05:43,055 --> 01:05:46,047
"Even the strongest have their
moments of fatigue."

905
01:05:46,525 --> 01:05:48,584
And I'm fatigued, Dan.

906
01:05:48,894 --> 01:05:51,328
I'm fucking fatigued. Oh, God.

907
01:06:08,080 --> 01:06:08,876
You okay?

908
01:06:09,448 --> 01:06:12,906
Do I look okay? I got a gun
pointed at the back of my head.

909
01:06:13,352 --> 01:06:14,683
Nice fucking pants.

910
01:06:14,887 --> 01:06:17,287
Shut up, Mr. Blackwell. Get over here.

911
01:06:21,494 --> 01:06:23,086
- You working?
- Sort of.

912
01:06:23,796 --> 01:06:26,697
I was negotiating a truce between
my wife and daughter.

913
01:06:26,899 --> 01:06:28,924
That might prove easy by comparison.

914
01:06:29,702 --> 01:06:31,670
It wouldn't surprise me in the least.

915
01:06:32,304 --> 01:06:33,498
You shut off the heat.

916
01:06:34,173 --> 01:06:35,765
You know how this works.

917
01:06:36,308 --> 01:06:37,468
Yeah, I do.

918
01:06:38,644 --> 01:06:41,670
Next time you try and bluff,
make sure you charge your cell phone.

919
01:06:42,948 --> 01:06:45,746
Now, you want to tell me
what I'm doing up here?

920
01:06:46,185 --> 01:06:49,052
I wanted to tell you face to face
I'm not crazy.

921
01:06:49,422 --> 01:06:51,583
I'm just doing this to
prove my innocence.

922
01:06:52,491 --> 01:06:55,119
I believe you.
Anything I can do to help you get out...

923
01:06:55,327 --> 01:06:56,624
Don't fucking patronize me!

924
01:06:57,463 --> 01:06:58,862
You don't think I'm innocent!

925
01:06:59,065 --> 01:07:02,262
Don't tell me "I want to do everything
I can to help you."

926
01:07:02,468 --> 01:07:04,527
Like I'm some second-rate HT.

927
01:07:04,770 --> 01:07:06,931
You're right. I'm sorry. My mistake.

928
01:07:07,206 --> 01:07:11,108
You are sorry. Get out. Lock the door.
Call when you want to talk.

929
01:07:11,343 --> 01:07:12,571
I'm ready to talk.

930
01:07:15,314 --> 01:07:16,372
You're right.

931
01:07:17,283 --> 01:07:18,113
You're right.

932
01:07:18,751 --> 01:07:20,946
I don't know if you're innocent or not.

933
01:07:21,220 --> 01:07:25,748
You could've done everything they say
you've done. I don't care.

934
01:07:25,991 --> 01:07:29,188
There are ways to prove your innocence.
This isn't one of them.

935
01:07:29,829 --> 01:07:31,922
And now you got hostages.

936
01:07:32,565 --> 01:07:33,623
So let me tell you:

937
01:07:34,166 --> 01:07:38,364
You hurt one of them, you'll burn up
whatever currency you got to deal with.

938
01:07:38,571 --> 01:07:42,337
They're all I care about. You leaving
here walking is a distant second.
